%N A116177 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k+3 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 2.
%C A116177 If k+3 has d digits, the concatenation is k//k+3 = 10^d*k+k+3 = m*(m+2), therefore k//k+4 = 10^d*k+k+4 = (m+1)^2, so there is a large overlap with A115437. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
